702601f-a.title: Brooklyn: 18th Avenue - 68th Street
702601f-a.text:
(1)
Eighteenth Ave., east side, at 68th Street. When 68th Street
joins Eighteenth with Nineteenth Aves., this house will be demolished,
as the street will run through the house. In 1857 to 1873 it was the
residence of D. Robert, later it became the Kallman Orphanage.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, another view.
March 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
